%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20riding%20high%2C%20but%20one%20strategist%20says%20economic%20optimism%20will%20eventually%20be%20cut%20short%20as%20unseen%20labor%20weakness%20bites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20Paul%20Dietrich%2C%20who%20warned%20that%20employment%20conditions%20are%20worse%20than%20analysts%20seem%20to%20grasp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEventually%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20will%20fall%20into%20a%20recession%2C%20catching%20off-guard%20the%20Fed%2C%20the%20US%20administration%2C%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20economists%20and%20analysts%2C%26quot%3B%20Dietrich%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrileyfin.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fwealth%2Findividual-client-services%2Fmarket-insights%2Fpaul-dietrich%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonthly%20commentary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20B.%20Riley%20Wealth%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20cited%20that%20September's%20jobless%20rate%20would%20have%20been%204.5%25%20if%20temporary%20government%20positions%20were%20eliminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20significantly%20higher%20than%20the%204.1%25%20rate%20published%20two%20weeks%20ago%2C%20a%20figure%20that%20convinced%20Wall%20Street%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20was%20doing%20better%20than%20originally%20feared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDietrich%20pointed%20out%20this%20year's%20significant%20jump%20in%20state%20and%20local%20government%20employment%2C%20adding%20to%20the%20job%20market's%20perception%20of%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20view%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20these%20positions%20came%20after%20%24500%20billion%20worth%20of%20COVID-era%20stimulus%20programs%20were%20finally%20delivered%20to%20regional%20governments%20this%20year%2C%20which%20rushed%20to%20use%20these%20funds%20on%20new%20positions%20before%20the%20September%2030th%20fiscal%20year-end%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20almost%20all%20of%20these%20jobs%20were%20listed%20as%20temporary%20jobs%2C%20and%20unless%20these%20gove