Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-cash-back-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ecash-back%20credit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20give%20a%20percentage%20back%20to%20your%20card%20based%20on%20how%20much%20you've%20spent.%20It's%20common%20to%20receive%201%25%20to%202%25%20back%20on%20cash-back%20cards.%20Some%20cards%20may%20have%20rotating%20categories%20in%20which%20you%20earn%20up%20to%203%25%20to%205%25%20back%20on%20specific%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fbest-rewards-credit-cards%5C%22%3ERewards%20credit%20cards%3C%2Fa%3E%20allow%20you%20to%20earn%20points%20or%20miles%20on%20every%20purchase%20rather%20than%20giving%20you%20cash%20back%20immediately.%20Depending%20on%20the%20category%2C%20these%20cards%20will%20offer%20a%20specific%20multiplier%20of%20points%20and%20miles.%20Strategically%20using%20credit%20cards%20this%20way%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20capitalize%20on%20your%20spending%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20love%20to%20travel%20like%20our%20family%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20favorite%20credit%20cards%20are%20the%20most%20flexible%20ones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20debating%20what%20type%20of%20credit%20card%20to%20open%20and%20use%20to%20earn%20points%20can%20be%20daunting%2C%20our%20family%20loves%20using%20credit%20cards%20that%20give%20you%20the%20most%20flexibility%20in%20redeeming%20those%20points.%20If%20you%20have%20a%20co-branded%20card%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fplatinum-delta-amex-card-review%5C%22%3EDelta%20Platinum%3C%2Fa%3E%20card%2C%20you%20can%20only%20use%20those%20points%20to%20fly%20Delta.%20However%2C%20you%20can%20redeem%20your%20points%20in%20many%20ways%20with%20a%20card%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fcapital-one-venture-x-rewards-credit-card-review%5C%22%3ECapital%20One%20Venture%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fchase-sapphire-preferred-card-review%5C%22%3EChase%20Sapphire%20Preferred%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Famex-gold-card-review%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Express%20Gold%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Once%20you%20have%20a%20collection%20of%20points%20to%20redeem%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20determine%20how%20to%20use%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20the%20travel%20rewards%20program%2C%20you%20can%20use%20points%20to%20erase%20travel-related%20or%20other%20charges%20you've%20racked%20up.%20You%20can%20also%20redeem%20points%20by%20purchasing%20gift%20cards%2C%20booking%20travel%20through%20the%20portal%2C%20or%20redeeming%20your%20miles%20for%20cash%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20transferring%20your%20points%20to%20a%20transfer%20airline%20or%20hotel%20partner%20can%20stretch%20those%20points%20even%20further.%20Most%20transfers%20occur%20at%20a%201%3A1%20ratio%2C%20meaning%20that%20one%20point%20will%20equal%20one%20mile%20when%20transferred.%20Beware%2C%20however%2C%20that%20some%20transfer%20partners%20offer%20less%20than%20a%201%3A1%20ratio.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20sometimes%20you%20can%20earn%20an%20even%20higher%20redemption%20rate%20when%20transferring%20to%20hotel%20and%20airline%20partners%20during%20what%20is%20known%20as%20a%20promotional%20transfer%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20saved%20on%20our%20trip%20to%20Europe%20by%20transferring%20points%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20a%20promotional%20transfer%20period%20is%20occurring%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20log%20in%20to%20check%20your%20specific%20credit%20card's%20updates%2C%20which%20you%20can%20usually%20do%20through%20your%20card's%20app%20or%20website.%20I've%20seen%20offers%20for%2025%25%20to%2050%25%20more%20points%20during%20a%20transfer%20promotion%20deal.%20When%20you%20search%20for%20a%20flight%20in%20a%20t