are%20just%20that%3A%20feelings.%20It%20can%20be%20tempting%20to%20categorize%20feelings%20as%20%26quot%3Bpositive%2Fgood%26quot%3B%20(like%20happiness%2C%20joy%2C%20pride)%20and%20%26quot%3Bnegative%2Fbad%26quot%3B%20(like%20sadness%2C%20anger%2C%20frustration)%20and%20conclude%20that%20we%20should%20seek%20to%20maximize%20the%20%26quot%3Bpositive%26quot%3B%20feelings%20and%20minimize%20the%20%26quot%3Bnegative%26quot%3B%20ones.%20But%20feelings%20aren't%20really%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeelings%20aren't%20bad%20and%20therefore%20to%20be%20avoided%2C%20or%20good%20and%20therefore%20to%20be%20sought%20after%3B%20feelings%20just%20are.%20Feelings%20are%20more%20like%20facts.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finherited-mother-in-law-after-husband-died-difficult-relationship-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20loved%20one%20dies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we%20feel%20sadness%20and%20grief%20and%20maybe%20anger.%20We%20get%20rejected%20from%20a%20program%20we%20worked%20hard%20to%20apply%20to%2C%20and%20we%20feel%20disappointed%2C%20frustrated%2C%20or%20defeated.%20Not%20every%20emotion%20can%20or%20should%20be%20immediately%20metabolized%20into%20something%20more%20palatable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20feel%20%26quot%3Bhappy%26quot%3B%20in%20response%20to%20simple%20events%20like%20seeing%20a%20beautiful%20sunset%2C%20hearing%20birds%20sing%2C%20smelling%20a%20fragrant%20flower%2C%20or%20learning%20it%20will%20be%20a%20cloudless%20night%20when%20we%20have%20scheduled%20to%20watch%20the%20Perseids%20meteor%20shower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20respond%20in%20a%20way%20that%20lets%20us%20appreciate%20these%20moments%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foverworked-years-until-child-realized-work-doesnt-care-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eputting%20down%20our%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20watch%20the%20sunset%20and%20remembering%20to%20literally%20smell%20the%20roses.%20But%20happiness%20is%20a%20fleeting%20feeling%20%E2%80%94%20all%20feelings%20are%20%E2%80%94%20and%20largely%20out%20of%20our%20control.%20We%20can't%20engineer%20these%20feelings%20of%20happiness%20to%20happen%20as%20frequently%20as%20we%20might%20like%2C%20and%20we%20certainly%20can't%20do%20it%20for%20our%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f21359d2-11bd-4f44-881a-71cc4e612519%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlways%20being%20happy%20is%20not%20the%20goal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20don't%20see%20our%20work%20as%20parents%20to%20be%20constantly%20monitoring%20our%20child's%20feelings%2C%20and%20working%20to%20ensure%20they%20are%20positive%2C%20at%20least%20a%20part%20of%20our%20work%20is%20to%20help%20our%20child%20to%20participate%20in%20meaningful%20work.%20For%20us%2C%20projects%20we%20work%20on%20together%20as%20a%20family%20are%20good%20models%20for%20the%20role%20of%20emotions%3A%20We're%20not%20always%20happy%20when%20we%20work%20together%20on%20a%20project.%20And%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20happy%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20an%20aim%20of%20our%20collaborative%20work.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20work%20usually%20involves%20difficult%2C%20objectionable%2C%20or%20tedious%20work%20(like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-smaller-house-decluttering-tips-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclearing%20out%20an%20attic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20removing%20wallpaper%2C%20cleaning%20out%20a%20drain%2C%20or%20taking%20a%20load%20of%20heavy%20bags%20to%20the%20dump).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20course%20of%20doing%20this%20work%2C%20we%20routinely%20run%20into%20frustrating%20complications%20and%20setbacks%2C%20and%20frequently%20enough%20we%20discover%20another%20involved%20project%20we'll%20need%20to%20tackle%20that%20we%20hadn't%20planned%20on%2C%20like%20when%20we%20were%20preparing%20to%20sand%20the%20floor%20in%20a%20room%2C%20only%20to%20discover%20that%20the%20floor%20needed%20to%20be%20replaced%20entirely.%20Our%20expectations%20aren't%20related%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccept-big-feelings-little-kids-normalize-same-for-parents-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echild's%20emotions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20rather%20to%20their%20participation.%20We%20try%20to%20show%20them%20how%20to%20participate%20and%20expect%20them%20to%20contribute%20meaningfully.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20of%20working%20together%20is%20usually%20increased%20competence%20in%20the%20specific%20work%20involved%20and%20competence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarting-business-with-partner-strengthened-relationship-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20with%20one%20another%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20best%20projects%2C%20when%20we%20can%20all%20see%20the%20difference%20our%20work%20has%20made%2C%20we%20experience%20a%20sense%20of%20satisfaction%20and%20fulfillment%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20satisfaction%20is%20rewarding%20and%20can%20be%20a%20partial%20motivator%20for%20future%20projects%2C%20it%20is%20definitely%20not%20the%20predominant%20feeling%20throughout.%20It%20is%20not%20the%20reason%20or%20justification%20for%20the%20work.%20It%20is%20mostly%20reserved%20for%20the%20very%20end.%20And%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20projects%20with%20no%20collective%20cheer%20of%20satisfaction%20at%20the%20end.%20But%20that's%20OK.%20It's%20a%20bad%20bargain%20to%20exchange%20the%20expectation%20of%20a%20continued%20feeling%20that%20is%20by%20nature%20fleeting%2C%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-married-my-high-school-sweetheart-18-years-ago-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenduring%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233e694f4-a4f5-4c21-973a-1ed55cf05473%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20embrace%20the%20unavoidable%20challenges%20of%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20are%20overly%20concerned%20that%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flove-having-an-only-child-benefits-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekids%20feel%20happy%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20the%20time%2C%20we%20might%20not%20ask%20them%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20difficult%20work%20where%20the%20sense%20of%20satisfaction%20and%20fulfillment%20comes%20only%20at%20the%20end.%20A%20more%20serious%20risk%20to%20insisting%20that%20a%20child%20is%20always%20happy%2C%20or%20believing%20that%2C%20ideally%2C%20a%20child%20should%20always%20or%20usually%20be%20happy%20%E2%80%94%20beyond%20its%20futility%20%E2%80%94%20is%20that%20it%20can%20ironically%20convey%20the%20message%20to%20our%20child%20that%20their%20%26quot%3Bhappiness%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20condition%20of%20our%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20much%20more%20valuable%20message%20to%20communicate%20with%20our%20children%20is%20that%2C%20because%20of%20our%20many%20shared%20experiences%20across%20a%20range%20of%20activities%20and%20emotions%2C%20we%20can%20trust%20and%20be%20at%20ease%20with%20one%20another%2C%20independent%20of%20our%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20message%20that%20depression%20(which%20we%20have%20personal%20experience%20with)%20communicates%20that%20is%20true%20is%20that%20life%20is%20hard.%20We%20all%20experience%20distress%20at%20work%20or%20school.%20We'll%20run%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychologist-realized-problem-toxic-relationships-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelationship%20drama%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20feelings%20will%20be%20hurt.%20We'll%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20pangs%20of%20regret%20because%20of%20things%20we%20said%20or%20did.%20We'll%20feel%20lonely%2C%20self-conscious%2C%20and%20bored.%20Along%20with%20these%20everyday%20hardships%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20real%20horror%20in%20the%20world.%20While%20violence%20and%20suffering%20have%20thankfully%20decreased%20over%20time%2C%20today%2C%20we're%20much%20more%20aware%20of%20incidents%20of%20violence%20and%20suffering%20than%20we%20ever%20could%20have%20been%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20political%20spectrum%2C%20people%2C%20including%20children%2C%20have%20become%20increasingly%20worried%20or%20pessimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20politics%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-political-violence-election-assassination-attempt-tipping-point-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolitical%20rhetoric%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20stoked%20these%20fears%20(even%20if%20only%20when%20imagining%20the%20opposing%20party%20winning).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20mean%20to%20be%20dramatic%20about%20this%20or%20to%20suggest%20that%20we%20should%20expect%20all%20children%20to%20be%20Eeyores%2C%20but%20this%20context%20can%20be%20a%20helpful%20check%20if%20we'd%20assumed%20that%20our%20children%20should%20always%2C%20or%20usually%2C%20be%20happy.%20There%20will%20be%20times%20when%20your%20child%20feels%20crummy%20about%20their%20future%2C%20and%20that's%20valid.%20They%20get%20to%20feel%20that%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20try%20to%20take%20those%20bad%20feelings%20away%2C%20even%20if%20it%20can%20be%20trying%20to%20sit%20with%20someone%20who%20is%20experiencing%20%26quot%3Bnegative%26quot%3B%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De6af50532b523e8c8d0500544386a4c630f168277540822b9ed0fd1622bc6b77%26postID%3D66f1bdd7d738168e48a523e6%26postSlug%3Dkids-emotions-acceptance-happiness-importance-2024-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FKids-Are-All-Right-Confidence%252Fdp%252F1523526505%252Fref%253Dpd_bxgy_d_sccl_1%252F144-5057923-6693353%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Kids%20Are%20All%20Right%3A%20Parenting%20with%20Confidence%20in%20an%20Uncertain%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem