t%20easy.%20(Read%20more%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fhigh-yield-savings-vs-high-yield-checking%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20versus%20high-yield%20checking%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EMoney%20Market%20Accounts%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-money-market-accounts%5C%22%3Ebest%20money%20market%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20considered%20a%20middle%20ground%20between%20checking%20and%20savings%3A%20They%20are%20used%20for%20saving%20money%20but%20typically%20provide%20easy%20access%20to%20your%20account%20through%20checks%20or%20a%20debit%20card.%20They%20usually%20offer%20a%20tiered%20interest%20rate%20depending%20on%20your%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECash%20Management%20Accounts%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fcash-management-account%5C%22%3Ecash%20management%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20like%20a%20savings%2Fchecking%20hybrid.%20You'll%20generally%20see%20them%20offered%20by%20online%20banks%2C%20and%2C%20unlike%20a%20checking%20account%2C%20they%20usually%20offer%20unlimited%20transfers.%20A%20savings%20account%20often%20limits%20the%20number%20of%20monthly%20transfers%2C%20while%20a%20checking%20account%20doesn't.%20Cash%20management%20accounts%20typically%20come%20with%20a%20debit%20card%20for%20easy%20access%2C%20but%20you%20may%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20fee%20if%20you%20want%20to%20deposit%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECertificates%20of%20Deposit%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20CD%20rates%20may%20outpace%20any%20of%20the%20other%20accounts%20we've%20described%20above.%20That's%20because%20a%20certificate%20of%20deposit%20requires%20you%20to%20%26quot%3Block%20in%26quot%3B%20your%20money%20for%20a%20predetermined%20amount%20of%20time%20ranging%20from%20three%20months%20to%20five%20years.%20To%20retrieve%20it%20before%20then%2C%20