0spectrum%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728987927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114248063%2Cimgsize-22742.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Felon-musk-joins-reliance-jio-airtel-vs-amazon-starlink-and-other-bif-members-fight-on-satellite-spectrum%2Farticleshow%2F114248115.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%20of%20Starlink%20joins%20the%20battle%20against%20Indian%20telecom%20giants%2C%20Reliance%20Jio%20and%20Bharti%20Airtel%2C%20over%20the%20allocation%20of%20satellite%20communication%20spectrum.%20Jio%20and%20Airtel%20advocate%20for%20spectrum%20auctions%20to%20ensure%20a%20level%20playing%20field%2C%20while%20Musk%20opposes%20this%2C%20citing%20ITU%20rules%20designating%20the%20spectrum%20as%20shared%20for%20satellites.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Felon-musk-joins-reliance-jio-airtel-vs-amazon-starlink-and-other-bif-members-fight-on-satellite-spectrum%2Farticleshow%2F114248115.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Opinion%20%7C%20India's%20Out-Of-Pocket%20Health%20Spend%20Is%20Decreasing.%20Here's%20How%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F05152915%2Fayush_hospitals_istock_660x330.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20Health%20Ministry's%20recently%20released%20National%20Health%20Accounts%20(NHA)%20estimates%20for%202020-21%20and%202021-22%20reveal%20several%20positive%20trends%20for%20India.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20substantial%20reduction%20in%20out-of-pocket%20expenditure%20(OOPE)%20in%20healthcare.%20Over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20OOPE%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20total%20health%20expenditure%20(THE)%20has%20sharply%20declined%20from%2064.2%25%20in%202013-14%20to%2039.4%25%20in%202021-22.%20This%20trend%20indicates%20a%20marked%20shift%20towards%20greater%20financial%20protection%20for%20citizens%2C%20as%20government%20interventions%20such%20as%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%20(PMJAY)%2C%20the%20Free%20Dialysis%20scheme%2C%20and%20other%20health%20programmes%20have%20increasingly%20shouldered%20the%20burden%20of%20healthcare%20costs.%20The%20introduction%20and%20expansion%20of%20these%20schemes%20have%20resulted%20in%20savings%20of%20more%20than%20%E2%82%B91%20lakh%20crore%20for%20beneficiaries%2C%20highlighting%20the%20government's%20proactive%20measures%20in%20alleviating%20the%20financial%20stress%20faced%20by%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20drop%20in%20OOPE%20is%20a%20significant%20achievement%20in%20India's%20march%20towards%20Universal%20Health%20Coverage%20(UHC).%20The%20improved%20methodology%20for%20NHA%20estimates%20over%20the%20years%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20more%20accurate%20and%20robust%20understanding%20of%20the%20government's%20healthcare%20expenditure.%20The%20reduction%20in%20OOPE%20also%20reflects%20the%20broader%20policy%20focus%20on%20expanding%20access%20to%20healthcare%20while%20reducing%20the%20financial%20strain%20on%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20noteworthy%20aspects%20of%20the%20NHA%20estimates%20is%20the%20consistent%20increase%20in%20government%20health%20expenditure%20(GHE)%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20both%20GDP%20and%20overall%20government%20spending.%20Between%202014-15%20and%202021-22%2C%20GHE%20has%20risen%20from%201.13%25%20of%20GDP%20to%201.84%25%2C%20and%20its%20share%20of%20general%20government%20expenditure%20has%20grown%20from%203.94%25%20to%206.12%25.%20In%20per%20capita%20terms%2C%20government%20health%20spending%20has%20tripled%2C%20from%20%E2%82%B91%2C108%20to%20%E2%82%B93%2C169%20during%20the%20same%20period%2C%20reflecting%20the%20government's%20growing%20commitment%20to%20public%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20provision%20of%20healthcare%20services%2C%20government%20hospitals%20account%20for%20Rs.%201%2C49%2C900%20crores%20(18.99%25%20of%20current%20health%20expenditure%20or%20CHE)%2C%20while%20private%20hospitals%20contribute%20Rs.%202%2C12%2C948%20crores%20(26.96%25%20of%20CHE).%20Expenditures%20on%20other%20government%20providers%2C%20such%20as%20Primary%20Health%20Centers%20(PHCs)%2C%20dispensaries%20and%20family%20planning%20centres%2C%20amount%20to%20Rs.%2056%2C477%20crore%20(7.15%25%20of%20CHE).%20Other%20private%20providers%2C%20including%20private%20clinics%2C%20account%20for%20Rs.%2030%2C080%20crore%20(3.81%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20while%20providers%20of%20patient%20transport%20and%20emergency%20rescue%20services%20contribute%20Rs.%2028%2C906%20crore%20(3.65%25%20of%20CHE).%20Medical%20and%20diagnostic%20laboratories%20make%20up%20Rs.%2026%2C238%20crore%20(3.32%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20pharmacies%20account%20for%20Rs.%201%2C52%2C910%20crore%20(19.35%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20and%20providers%20of%20preventive%20care%20contribute%20Rs.%2082%2C325%20crore%20(10.42%25%20of%20CHE).%20Additionally%2C%20Rs.%2027%2C380%20crore%20(3.48%25%20of%20CHE)%20are%20allocated%20to%20health%20system%20administration%2C%20and%20other%20healthcare%20providers%20account%20for%20Rs.%2021%2C759%20crore%20(2.76%25%20of%20CHE).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20services%20consumed%2C%20inpatient%20curative%20care%20represents%20Rs.%202%2C99%2C587%20crore%20(37.94%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20while%20outpatient%20curative%20care%20accounts%20for%20Rs.%201%2C20%2C816%20crore%20(15.30%25%20of%20CHE).%20Patient%20transportation%20services%20total%20Rs.%2028%2C906%20crore%20(3.65%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20laboratory%20and%20imaging%20services%20amount%20to%20Rs.%2026%2C238%20crore%20(3.32%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20and%20prescribed%20medicines%20account%20for%20Rs.%201%2C26%2C225%20crore%20(15.98%25%20of%20CHE).%20Preventive%20care%20makes%20up%20Rs.%201%2C07%2C048%20crore%20(13.55%25%20of%20CHE)%2C%20and%20traditional%2C%20complementary%2C%20and%20alternative%20medicine%20(TCAM)%20expenditures%20are%203.59%25%20of%20CHE.%20The%20overall%20current%20health%20expenditure%20is%20distributed%20among%20primary%20care%20(46%25)%2C%20secondary%20care%20(33%25)%2C%20and%20tertiary%20care%20(16%25)%2C%20with%20the%20government's%20spending%20weighted%20more%20towards%20primary%20care%20(50%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20rise%20in%20government%20spending%20on%20health%20has%20important%20long-term%20implications%20for%20India's%20healthcare%20system.%20First%2C%20it%20enhances%20the%20country's%20ability%20to%20tackle%20not%20just%20immediate%20health%20crises%2C%20such%20as%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20but%20also%20long-term%20challenges%20like%20non-communicable%20diseases%20(NCDs)%2C%20which%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20Higher%20public%20spending%20on%20health%20can%20also%20translate%20into%20improved%20infrastructure%2C%20better-trained%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20and%20more%20accessible%20healthcare%20services%2C%20particularly%20in%20rural%20and%20underserved%20regions.%20Over%20time%2C%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20stronger%2C%20more%20resilient%20healthcare%20system%20capable%20of%20handling%20both%20routine%20care%20and%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20critical%20component%20of%20the%20decline%20in%20OOPE%20has%20been%20the%20rise%20in%20Social%20Security%20Expenditure%20(SSE)%20on%20healthcare%2C%20which%20includes%20government-funded%20health%20insurance%20and%20social%20health%20programmes.%20The%20SSE's%20share%20of%20THE%20has%20increased%20from%205.7%25%20in%202014-15%20to%208.7%25%20in%202021-22.%20This%20expansion%20of%20social%20security%20nets%20ensures%20that%20individuals%20are%20protected%20from%20catastrophic%20health%20expenditures%20and%20do%20not%20face%20financial%20ruin%20when%20accessing%20essential%20healthcare%20services.%20With%20more%20comprehensive%20health%20insurance%20coverage%20and%20financial%20safeguards%20in%20place%2C%20fewer%20households%20will%20be%20pushed%20into%20poverty%20due%20to%20healthcare%20costs%2C%20which%20have%20historically%20been%20a%20major%20concern%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%2C%20the%20continued%20reduction%20in%20OOPE%20and%20increased%20government%20health%20spending%20could%20have%20significant%20future%20implications%20for%20India's%20health%20outcomes%20and%20socio-economic%20development.%20As%20the%20government%20continues%20to%20invest%20in%20healthcare%2C%20it%20is%20expected%20that%20health%20indicators%2C%20such%20as%20life%20expectancy%2C%20infant%20and%20maternal%20mortality%20rates%2C%20and%20overall%20morbidity%2C%20will%20improve.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20more%20productive%20workforce%2C%20fewer%20days%20lost%20to%20illness%2C%20and%20greater%20economic%20growth.%20Improved%20health%20outcomes%20are%20also%20likely%20to%20reduce%20the%20overall%20healthcare%20burden%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20as%20preventive%20care%20and%20early%20intervention%20become%20more%20accessible%2C%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20costly%20tertiary%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20these%20trends%20suggest%20a%20gradual%20shift%20towards%20a%20healthcare%20system%20that%20prioritises%20financial%20protection%20and%20equity.%20As%20the%20government%20continues%20to%20expand%20its%20role%20in%20healthcare%20financing%2C%20it%20will%20be%20crucial%20to%20ensure%20that%20these%20gains%20are%20not%20just%20maintained%20but%20further%20strengthened.%20Policy%20focus%20should%20now%20pivot%20towards%20enhancing%20the%20quality%20of%20care%2C%20improving%20efficiency%20in%20healthcare%20delivery%2C%20and%20ensuring%20that%20healthcare%20services%20remain%20accessible%20and%20affordable%20for%20all.%20This%20will%20require%20continued%20investment%20in%20healthcare%20infrastructure%2C%20human%20resources%2C%20and%20technology%20to%20bridge%20the%20gaps%20in%20care%20quality%20across%20different%20regions%20and%20socio-economic%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NHA%20estimates%20for%202020-21%20and%202021-22%20highlight%20a%20positive%20trajectory%20for%20India's%20healthcare%20financing%20system%2C%20with%20declining%20OOPE%2C%20rising%20government%20health%20expenditure%2C%20and%20a%20more%20robust%20social%20security%20framework.%20These%20trends%20are%20promising%2C%20but%20sustaining%20and%20building%20on%20them%20will%20require%20continued%20political%20will%2C%20smart%20policy%20interventions%2C%20and%20a%20focus%20on%20equity%20and%20quality%20of%20care.%20The%20government's%20commitment%20to%20increasing%20public%20health%20investments%20provides%20a%20solid%20foundation%2C%20but%20future%20efforts%20must%20ensure%20that%20these%20resources%20are%20effectively%20utilised%20to%20improve%20health%20outcomes%20and%20ensure%20that%20every%20citizen%2C%20regardless%20of%20their%20socio-economic%20status%2C%20has%20access%20to%20affordable%2C%20high-quality%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20is%20Chairman%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20and%20Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20OSD%2C%20Research%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728987900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fsites%2F3%2F2024%2F03%2F05152915%2Fayush_hospitals_istock_660x330.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-out-of-pocket-health-spend-is-decreasing-6794126%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government's%20commitment%20to%20increasing%20public%20health%20investments%20provides%20a%20solid%20foundation%2C%20but%20future%20efforts%20must%20ensure%20that%20these%20resour